item.title: Marlene Clark, Sanford and Son Actress, Dies at 85
item.description: Sanford and Son actress Marlene Clark has died at the age of 85. Her friend Tamara Lynch told People magazine that the actress died in her home in Los Angeles on May 18—the same day her Slaughter co-star Jim Brown died. She is perhaps best known for her role as Lamont’s (Demond Wilson) girlfriend in Sanford and Son. Wilson paid tribute to Clark on Twitter. “RIP beautiful actress Marlene Clark,” Wilson posted.
